9. Qxd4 Bc5 10. Qd3 b5 11. f4 Bb7 12. Bf3 O-O (12... h5 {with the idea of ..
Ng4 is a bit more adventurous - and it's also a line with a good plus score
for Black.}) 13. e5 Ne8 14. a4 $146 {Taking on b7 and either f5 or Ne4 is par
for the course here - usually White doesn't commit the queenside pawns.} 14...
b4 15. Bxb7 Qxb7 16. Ne4 Be7 17. Be3 Qc6 18. Ng5 g6 (18... Bxg5 $6 19. fxg5 Rc8
20. Bd2 $1 (20. Rac1 d6 $1) 20... a5 (20... Qxc2 $2 21. Qxc2 Rxc2 22. Bxb4) 21.
