19. Rad1 d6 20. Bd4 dxe5 21. Bxe5 Nf6 22. Qh3 h5 23. Nf3 ({
Bluff?  I thought defending c2 with} 23. Qb3 {was the only way.}) 23... Ng4 (
23... Qxc2 $5 {After a good, long think.  I don't know what spooked Judit, but
taking on c2 looked good; what does White have?} 24. Nd4 (24. a5 Ng4 $1) 24...
Qxa4 25. f5 (25. Qh4 Nd5 $1) (25. Qd3 Qe8 $1 {a little awkward, but two pawns
are two pawns and Black should be able to untangle herself.}) 25... Ng4 $1 ({
Could this be what Judit missed? Apart from attacking the bishop on e5, Ng4
also threatens ..Qxd1 followed by a knight fork on f2.  This just looks good
