now you can take on f5 as the piece sac doesn't work anymore as there's no Qh4.
}) 24. Nd4 Qc5 25. Qg3 Rad8 26. c3 bxc3 27. bxc3 Rd5 28. Rde1 Rc8 29. Rf3 Bf8
30. h3 Nxe5 31. fxe5 Bg7 32. Rfe3 Qa5 $2 ({Time trouble -} 32... Qc7 $1 {
, not only keep's the pressure on e5, but also indirectly defending her king:}
33. Qf4 (33. Nxe6 $2 fxe6 34. Qxg6 Qf7 $1) 33... Rc5 $1 {and somethings got to
