moves to survive.} 38... Qb7 39. Qxe6+ Kh8 (39... Kh7 40. Rf7 Rxe5 41. Qf6 $1)
40. Qe8+ Kh7 41. Qxh5+ Kg8 42. Qe8+ Kh7 43. Rf7 Rd8 $1 {To be fair, this move
was spotted by someone whom Lubosh Kavalek once stated: "Before Fritz, we had
